{{ja-noun|かみ}}

# {{context|lang=ja|sort=かみ|archaic}} under the old {{w|Ritsuryō}} system of ancient Japan, the highest of the four ranks of [[civil servant]] staff, and general term for head [[administrator]]s of government departments
# {{context|lang=ja|sort=かみ|archaic}} in the first year of the new {{w|Meiji era}} government established in 1868, the [[title]] of the seven heads of all government [[bureau]]s except the {{term|lang=ja|総裁局|tr=Sōsai Kyoku||Bureau of the President}}, whose head was titled {{term|lang=ja|総裁|tr=Sōsai||president” or “director general}}

